Excellent overview of testing debacle. Key takeaways:
- US labs could have begun making their own tests in mid-Jan
- But kept from doing so by FDA & CDC policy and regulatory barriers
- Not just CDC technical failure but an interagency coordination failure https://t.co/MUGwOUoiY3

Truly stunning to hear some Republicans advocate for free Coronavirus testing and treatment for the uninsured.

Rep. Ted Yoho (R-Fla.), one of the most anti-ACA members:

“You can look at it as socialized medicine, but in the face of an outbreak, a pandemic, what’s your options?”

Truly stunning to hear some Republicans advocate for free Coronavirus testing and treatment for the uninsured.
